The '''Archaeological Society of Athens''' ([[Greek language|Greek]]: ŒïŒΩ ŒëŒ∏ŒÆŒΩŒ±ŒπœÇ ŒëœÅœáŒ±ŒπŒøŒªŒøŒ≥ŒπŒ∫ŒÆ ŒïœÑŒ±ŒπœÅŒµŒØŒ±) is an independent [[learned society]].[http://www.archetai.gr/site/eng_page_uc.html] Also termed the '''Greek Archaeological Society''', it was founded in 1837, just a few years after the establishment of the modern Greek State, with the aim of encouraging [[Excavation (archaeology)|archaeological excavations]], maintenance, care and exhibition of antiquities in [[Greece]].

