[[File:Knygu-muge2009-litexpo.jpg|thumb|[[Vilnius Book Fair]] 2009 in LITEXPO]]
'''LITEXPO''' (from ''Lit''huanian ''expo''sition) or '''Lithuanian Exhibition and Congress Centre''' ({{lang-lt|Lietuvos parod≈≥ ir kongres≈≥ centras}}), located in [[Vilnius]], [[Lithuania]], is the largest exhibition centre in the [[Baltic states]].<ref>[http://www.culturelive.lt/en/2009/events2009-special/bookfair/ Vilnius Book Fair] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015105448/http://www.culturelive.lt/en/2009/events2009-special/bookfair/ |date=2012-10-15 }}. Retrieved in 2009-02-14</ref> 

It offers nine exhibition halls with a combined area of {{convert|17600|m2}} and outdoor area of {{convert|15100|m2}}. Biggest hall have capacity of 1.800, while capacity of whole centre is 8.000 people.<ref>[http://vz.lt/article/2014/1/15/vien-litexpo-lietuvai-nebeuztenka Vien ‚ÄûLitexpo‚Äú Lietuvai nebeu≈ætenka]</ref>

LITEXPO organizes over twenty international exhibitions annually, including Resta (construction fair) and [[Vilnius Book Fair]]. It also organizes conferences and other special events. In December 2011, LITEXPO hosted Ministerial Council meeting of the [[Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe]]. The [[Ministry of Economy (Lithuania)|Ministry of Economy]] owns more than 98% of the shares in LITEXPO.<ref>[http://www.litexpo.lt/repository/Metine%20ataskaita%202011.pdf 2011 m. finansinƒó ir veiklos ataskaita]</ref>

