===Infraclass: [[Eutheria]]===
====Order: [[Chiroptera]] (bats)==== ---- [[Image:Tadarida brasiliensis - Bahamas - Long Island (sic) - Cartwright Cave - March 2006 - 2.jpg|thumb|[[Mexican Free-tailed Bat]]]] The bats' most distinguishing feature is that their forelimbs are developed as wings, making them the only mammals in the world naturally capable of flight. Bat species account for about 20% of all mammals.
*Family: [[Molossidae]] **Genus: [[Tadarida]] *** [[Mexican free-tailed bat]] ''Tadarida brasiliensis'' LR/nt
====Order: [[Cetacea]] (whales)==== ---- [[Image:Balaenoptera borealis 3.jpg|thumb|[[Sei whale]]]] [[Image:Dolphin leaping out of the ocean (5656231914).jpg|thumb|[[Peale's dolphin]] [[cetacean surfacing behavior|jumping]] near [[Stanley, Falkland Islands|Stanley]]]] [[Image:Anim1763 - Flickr - NOAA Photo Library.jpg|thumb|[[Dusky dolphin]]]] [[Image:Commersons Dolphins off Saunders Island (5551645921).jpg|thumb|[[Commerson's dolphin]]s at [[Saunders Island, Falkland Islands|Saunders Island]]]] The order Cetacea includes [[whale]]s, [[dolphin]]s and [[porpoise]]s. They are the mammals most fully [[aquatic adaptation|adapted to aquatic]] life with a spindle-shaped nearly hairless body, protected by a thick layer of blubber, and forelimbs and tail modified to provide propulsion underwater.
