The '''Union for National Salvation''' ({{lang-fr|Union pour le Salut National}} '''USN''') is a political coalition in [[Djibouti]].
Led by [[Ahmed Youssof Houmed]], the coalition was formed to contest the [[Djiboutian parliamentary election, 2013|2013 parliamentary election]].<ref name="FB Info">{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/USNDJIBOUTI/info|title=Union pour le Salut National - USN Djibouti|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-17}}</ref> The party won 21 seats in the election, although the USN cited what it referred to as cases of mass fraud and [[ballot tampering]], and called for demonstrations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.jeuneafrique.com/Article/JA2721p040.xml0/|title=Djibouti : l‚Äôopposition fait son entr√©e √† l‚ÄôAssembl√©e ‚Äì JeuneAfrique.com|date=2013-03-11|work=JeuneAfrique.com|access-date=2017-09-17|language=fr-FR}}</ref>
The coalition is composed of six parties; the [[Republican Alliance for Democracy|ARD]], the [[Djibouti Union for Democracy and Justice|UDJ]], the [[Movement for Democratic Renewal and Development|MRD]], the [[National Democratic Party (Djibouti)|PND]], and the [[Djibouti Party for Development|PDD]], and [[Movement for Developement and Freedom|MoDel]].<ref name="FB Info"/>
